6. Projectionist mapping for directory structure.
A. [Refer: See Greg Hurrell vim screencast video on youtube]

  Dir structure:
   |--Component
     |--component.js
     |--component.spec.js
     |--component.scss

   In vimrc:
     `
     let g:projectionist_heuristics = {
       \"*": {
	 \"*.js": {
	   \"alternate": [
	     \"{}.spec.js",
	   \"{}.scss"
	     \],
	     \"type": "source"
	       \},
	 \"*.spec.js": {
	   \  "alternate": [
	     \"{}.scss",
	   \"{}.js"
	     \],
	     \  "type": "test"
	       \  },
	 \"*.scss": {
	   \  "alternate": [
	     \"{}.js",
	   \"{}.test.js"
	     \],
	     \  "type": "style"
	       \}
	 \}
	 \}
	 `
